         <div type="edition">
                <!-- The marked up transcription goes here, surrounded by <ab> </ab> elements -->
            <ab>
               <lb n="1"/>
               <expan><abbr>D</abbr><ex>is</ex></expan>
               <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>anibus</ex></expan>.
                    <lb n="2"/>
               <persName>
                  <name type="gentilicium" key="Aurelia">Aureliae</name>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Marciana">Marcia<hi rend="small">n</hi><hi rend="ligature">ae</hi>
                  </name>
               </persName>
               <lb n="3"/>inconparabili femi
                    <lb n="4" break="no"/>nae quae vixit annis
                    <lb n="5"/>
               <num xml:lang="lat" value="25">XXV</num> et mensis <num xml:lang="lat" value="7">VII</num>.
                    <lb n="6"/>
               <persName>
                  <name type="praenomen" key="Marcus">
                     <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>arcus</ex></expan>
                  </name>
                  <name type="gentilicium" key="Aurelius"><expan><abbr>Aur</abbr><ex>elius</ex></expan></name>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Ptolemaeus">Ptolemaeus</name>
               </persName>
               <lb n="7"/>
               <expan><abbr>co</abbr><ex>n</ex><abbr>iugi</abbr></expan> mirenti
                    <lb n="8"/>suae hoc scripsit
                    <lb n="9"/>et ceteris liberis
                    <lb n="10"/>libertisque eius.</ab>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>To the Divine Spirits. To Aurelia Marciana, peerless woman, who lived for
               twenty-five years and seven months. Marcus Aurelius Ptolemaeus wrote this for his
               deserving wife and also for (his) children and for his freedmen. </p>
         </div>
